      </div>
    
    
      
      
           
      <div>


        <p>This resource tackles road safety and citizenship issues and looks at the positive and negative impacts of different forms of media.</p>
        <h2>Materials</h2>
        <h3>Filmed scenarios</h3>
        <p>There are three filmed scenarios.</p>
        <h3>Workshop films</h3>
        <p>Students can explore the messages in each scenario and are then encouraged to produce a performance and conduct their own surveys.</p>
        <h3>Media tools</h3>
        <p>You can download films and audio, scripts, information sheets and posters.</p>
        <h3>Interactive games</h3>
        <p>Students can participate in an engaging pairs game with 4 sub-games.</p>
        <h3>Teachers' notes</h3>
        <p>This is a guide to using the resource, plus extension activities linked into curriculum subjects of English, Drama, PSHE and Citizenship.</p>
        <p>If you are a teacher and would like to request this resource for a London school, please email <a href="mailto:educationandtraining&#64;tfl.gov.uk?Subject=Life's%20Journey">educationandtraining&#64;tfl.gov.uk</a> with your name, email and phone number; school name and address and school contact.</p>
    
